{"id": "EUVD-2025-198890", "enisaUuid": "1332d769-4898-33b5-b930-ffd7052c993e", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nBluetooth: MGMT: fix crash in set_mesh_sync and set_mesh_complete\n\nThere is a BUG: KASAN: stack-out-of-bounds in set_mesh_sync due to\nmemcpy from badly declared on-stack flexible array.\n\nAnother crash is in set_mesh_complete() due to double list_del via\nmgmt_pending_valid + mgmt_pending_remove.\n\nUse DEFINE_FLEX to declare the flexible array right, and don't memcpy\noutside bounds.\n\nAs mgmt_pending_valid removes the cmd from list, use mgmt_pending_free,\nand also report status on error.", "datePublished": "2025-11-24T15:59:44", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-01T06:20:19", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5c19daa93d9af29f1f46251b47e1ea66bcc8d679", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1c9aca1787e8395a2c59fef20e914467958969c5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e8785404de06a69d89dcdd1e9a0b6ea42dc6d327", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40213"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40213"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "00bbdb4b-06c0-313c-82bf-3627935f0b23", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d71b98f253b079cbadc83266383f26fe7e9e103b <5c19daa93d9af29f1f46251b47e1ea66bcc8d679"}, {"id": "49cb7dbb-b417-38bd-88e2-deb42f9813e1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "302a1f674c00dd5581ab8e493ef44767c5101aab <1c9aca1787e8395a2c59fef20e914467958969c5"}, {"id": "5935e468-c671-3265-b4d9-cc6af7fe944d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "87a1f16f07c6c43771754075e08f45b41d237421"}, {"id": "8b649aec-7b5c-3bc9-8dee-28e42dbeeca6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18"}, {"id": "9ad9c715-3bd4-3850-ad8a-8d8e17c2fda0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.17"}, {"id": "9ca49ec4-91b5-34a4-8fb0-070452fcaef4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "302a1f674c00dd5581ab8e493ef44767c